The vi/vim editor

vi [file]

or 

vim [file] to start editing a file

view [file] to only read a file


Vim Command Mode and Navigation

k           up one line
j           Down one line
h           Left one character
l           Right one character
w           Right one word
b           Left one word
^           Go to the beginning of the file
$           Go to the end of the file


Vi Insert Mode:

i         Insert at the cursor position
I         Insert at the beginning of the file
a         Append after the cursor position
A         Append at the End of the line


Vi Line Mode:

:w        Writes(saves) the file
:w!       forces the file to be saved
:q        Quit the file
:q!       Quit without savin any changes
:wq!      Wrtie and Quit
:x        Wrtie and Quit
:n        To position cursor at the value of the line n, eg :23
:$        Position cursor at the end of the Line

:set nu   Turn on line numbering
:set nonu Turn off line numbering

:help [subcommand] Get help

Manipulate Vi Modes:

Command Modes     Esc
Insert            ilaA
line              :

Vi Repeating Commands

- Repeat a command by preceding it with a number.
      => 5k = Move up a line 5 times
      => 80i <Text>  <ESC> = Insert <text> 80 times
      => 80i_<ESC> = Inset80"_" characters

Vi Deleting the text:
x         Delete a character   
dw        Delete a word
dd        delete a Line
D         Delete from current position

Vi Deleting the text:

r         Replace the current Text
cw        Change the current word
cc        Change the current Line
c$        Change the text from current position 
C         Change the text from current position
~         Reverse the case of a character

Vi Copying and Pasting

yy            Yank(copy) the current Line
y<position>   Yank the position

p             Paste the most recent deleted or yanked Text


Vi Undo/Redo

u           Undo
Ctrl-R      Redo

Vi Searching
/<pattern>  Start a forward Search
?<pattern>  Start a reverse

vimtutor is command for vim tutorial manual




  
